//! Orchestration for the `aberp serve` subcommand (PR-9-1).
//!
//! Realizes ADR-0021 ¬ßPart B's wire protocol decision: HTTPS+JSON over
//! a loopback listener. The Tauri/Svelte shell that lands in PR-9-2
//! consumes these routes.
//!
//! # What this PR lands
//!
//!   - A `127.0.0.1` HTTPS listener on a configurable port (default
//!     `0` ‚Äî kernel picks an unused one and the chosen port is
//!     printed for the operator to copy into the Tauri shell's
//!     bootstrap).
//!   - A self-signed certificate generated by `rcgen` at first launch
//!     and persisted next to the keychain material per ADR-0007
//!     ¬ßTransport. Subsequent launches reuse the persisted cert; the
//!     cert SHA-256 fingerprint is also persisted alongside in a
//!     plain-text file that the Tauri shell reads at startup to
//!     verify the handshake (per ADR-0007 ¬ßTransport).
//!   - Bearer-token authentication on every route except `/health`.
//!     The session token is derived from the OS keychain material
//!     (one new keychain item per tenant ‚Äî same `aberp.nav.<tenant>`
//!     service name as the NAV creds, key `session_token`) so the
//!     Tauri shell can pick it up alongside the existing creds.
//!   - Read-only routes only ‚Äî every mutation already lives in a CLI
//!     subcommand. The SPA in PR-9-2 will shell out to those for
//!     mutations until the operator-action routes land later. Per
//!     CLAUDE.md rule 2: minimum code, no speculative abstractions.
//!
//! # Routes
//!
//!   - `GET /health` ‚Äî unauthenticated; returns
//!     `{"ok":true,"binary_hash":"‚Ä¶","nav_xsd_version":"3.0"}`.
//!   - `GET /invoices?tenant=<id>` ‚Äî authenticated; returns the list
//!     of invoices in the tenant DB with their derived state per
//!     ADR-0009 ¬ß2.
//!   - `GET /invoices/<id>?tenant=<id>` ‚Äî authenticated; returns the
//!     single invoice plus its full audit-ledger trail.
//!   - `GET /audit/<invoice_id>?tenant=<id>` ‚Äî authenticated; returns
//!     just the audit-ledger entries for one invoice. The Tauri shell
//!     uses this for the per-invoice evidence-bundle view per
//!     ADR-0009 ¬ß8.
//!
//! # What this flow does NOT do
//!
//!   - No mutation endpoints (issue / submit / poll / retry /
//!     mark-abandoned). Those continue to be CLI subcommands until
//!     the SPA wants them on the API surface.
//!   - No fingerprint-pinning verification on the client side ‚Äî that
//!     belongs to the Tauri shell that lands in PR-9-2. The server
//!     publishes the fingerprint; verifying it is the client's job.
//!   - No session-token rotation flow yet ‚Äî one persisted token per
//!     tenant. A rotation command (`aberp rotate-session-token`)
//!     lands when the SPA first asks for it.
//!
//! # Failure-mode posture
//!
//!   - 401 Unauthorized for any non-`/health` route without a valid
//!     `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header.
//!   - 404 Not Found for unknown invoice ids ‚Äî the audit ledger has
//!     no canonical "invoice does not exist" signal beyond the absence
//!     of any entry for it, so the route returns 404 if the billing
//!     row is not found AND the audit ledger has zero entries for the
//!     id.
//!   - 500 Internal Server Error for any propagated `anyhow::Error`
//!     from the read paths ‚Äî surfaces loud per CLAUDE.md rule 12.
//!     The error message in JSON is sanitised to "internal error"; the
//!     real error goes to `tracing::error!`.

